already strong team that expects both technical credibility and leadership clarity.</li><li><strong>Architectural Depth – Event-Driven Systems: </strong>Strong track record with event-based or microservices architectures, ensuring scalability and reliability.</li><li>Why it matters: Our product requires real-time performance and enterprise-grade resilience.</li><li><strong>Product-Focused Mindset / First-Principles Thinking: </strong>Ability to translate business needs into technical solutions, making pragmatic trade-offs between <strong>quality, value, and time</strong>.</li><li>Why it matters: As we scale, shipping the right things at the right time will define our success.</li><li><strong>Remote Team Leadership: </strong>Proven ability to lead distributed engineering teams, balancing async and real-time collaboration, ensuring clarity, accountability, and belonging.</li><li>Why it matters: Our team is already international, and scaling further requires remote leadership excellence.</li><li><strong>AI-Native Engineering Approach: </strong>Passion for leveraging AI to automate code generation, testing, documentation, and deployment.</li><li>Sees AI not just as a tool, but as a <strong>paradigm shift</strong> in how software is designed and built.</li><li><strong>Additional Pluses: </strong>Scala experience.</li><li>Infra / Ops experience.</li><li>Track record of embracing KISS and design-to-time approaches.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>Role Details</p><ul><li><strong>Compensation</strong>: Competitive package with significant equity (BSPCE).</li><li><strong>Start Date</strong>: ASAP.</li><li><strong>Location</strong>: Paris preferred; flexible remote for exceptional candidates (±2 hours CET).</li><li><strong>Language</strong>: English required; French a plus.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>About Us</p><p>We’re building the <strong>business network of the future</strong>—a unified SaaS platform that merges Intake-to-Pay (I2P) and Order-to-Cash (O2C) into one seamless, AI-powered environment.</p><p>🌟 We’re proud to share that Flowie has been <strong>officially recognized by Gartner</strong> as a leading provider in the emerging category of <strong>Procurement Orchestration Platforms</strong> — a powerful validation of our vision and the incredible work of our team.</p><p>But our ambition goes beyond procurement. We are building a platform that could enable the world to truly <strong>understand what we are buying</strong> — by chaining supply data end-to-end. This means not only improving efficiency for enterprises, but also empowering society with <strong>transparency, sustainability, and accountability</strong> in global supply chains.</p><ul><li><strong>Global Ambition</strong> → Already operating in 3 countries, with 40 more on the roadmap.</li><li><strong>Proven Traction</strong> → From 0 to international enterprise clients in record time.</li><li><strong>AI at the Core</strong> → Automating, analyzing, and enabling smarter business decisions.</li><li><strong>Diverse &amp; Remote-Friendly</strong> → A team of 6+ nationalities, working across Europe, with a culture of ownership and excellence.</li><li><strong>Committed to Responsibility</strong> → ESG is part of our DNA: we are <strong>B Corp pending</strong>, engaged in <strong>Ecovadis certification</strong>, and committed to building a sustainable, ethical, and inclusive company.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>Our Stack</p><p>We run on a modern, event-driven architecture built for scale:</p><ul><li><strong>Backend</strong> → Scala, Node.js, Python macroservices</li><li><strong>Frontend</strong> → React, TypeScript (PWA)</li><li><strong>Events &amp; Data</strong> → Apache Pulsar, PostgreSQL, BigQuery, Neo4j</li><li><strong>Infrastructure</strong> → Kubernetes (GCP/Thales), Terraform</li><li><strong>Ops &amp; CI/CD</strong> → GitHub Actions, Sentry, Claude code, …</li><li><strong>AI &amp; GenAI</strong> → OpenAI, Anthropic, Mistral, Llama, Claude, orchestrated via MCP Server</li></ul><p>As CTO, you will <strong>own the evolution of this stack</strong> — ensuring it can scale 10x in the next 2 years while embracing <strong>AI-native workflows</strong> from product to deployment.</p><p><br></p><p>Why You Should Join</p><ul><li><strong>Impact from Day One</strong> → Lead a team of 11 engineers, shaping how we scale technically and culturally.</li><li><strong>Tech Visionary Role</strong> → Define the architecture and delivery model of a company about to 10x in the next 2 years.</li><li><strong>Equity &amp; Ownership</strong> → Significant participation in the upside you’ll help create.</li><li><strong>AI-Driven Future</strong> → Be at the forefront of AI-assisted engineering, pioneering automation from product specs to production.</li><li><strong>Global Supply Transparency</strong> → Help build the platform that could redefine how the world understands supply chains, with massive implications for <strong>ESG, compliance, and sustainability</strong>.</li><li><strong>Remote Leadership</strong> → Build and scale a distributed team across Europe, mastering async collaboration while keeping a strong culture.</li><li><strong>Culture of Builders</strong> → We value curiosity, resilience, and bold thinking—this is the place for ambitious minds unafraid of the impossible.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>Application Process</p><p>We keep it lean and respectful of your time:</p><ol><li><strong>CEO Call (45 min)</strong> → Vision &amp; mutual fit.</li><li><strong>Technical &amp; Product Case (1h30)</strong> → Real-world architecture + trade-offs.</li><li><strong>Leadership &amp; Team Fit (1h)</strong> → Meet engineers, test mutual chemistry.</li><li><strong>Final Alignment (1h)</strong> → Strategy, culture, equity.</li></ol><p><br></p><p>Join us at Flowie to shape the future of B2B collaboration, where we empower companies and foster sustainable growth through innovative solutions.</p><p><br></p><p>If you're hesitating, we encourage you to apply anyway: worst