ill focus on shaping and executing on the current and future digital commercialization strategies by managing the digital sales and utilization team in the assigned region. The digital sales and utilization team consists of Digital Sales Representatives (DSR) and Digital Solutions Integration Specialists (DSIS).The DSM will expand the footprint of Intuitive’ s digital products by promoting enhanced digital solutions to customers, turning opportunities into action and maximize digital solutions adoption and utilization.The DSM will regularly lead and facilitate meetings, build solid relationships, solve critical business challenges, and create new programs and processes with the goal of advancing customer engagement and satisfaction. In addition, the DSM will be critical in goal settings and forecasting and will provide regular updates to the top leadership in Europe.The DSM remains open to include other existing digital solutions, that may benefit from regrouping into the current portfolio or to include future digital solutions, as they are being brought to market. The DSM adapts quickly to continuous changes in a digital organization that evolves quickly over time.This field-based position requires 2-4 days per week travelling or being present with customers and teams across the assigned region.Roles &amp; ResponsibilitiesManage a highly motivated digital sales team by hiring, training, developing, and retaining top talent to drive the digital sales activities within the assigned region,Manage all commercial activities, from lead generation to closing the deal and post sales account management,Provide technical, functional and product expertise to team members,Execute the digital sales strategy in the assigned region, by developing and implementing sales activities to achieve and exceed goals set by senior management,Expand usage of digital in digital accounts,Manage and increase the day-to-day customer and account relations,Build and maintain excellent relationshi