 operational environments, dynamic backlogs, and on-call rotations.</li><li>You are pragmatic and data-driven.</li><li>You prioritize people and relationships, showing servant leadership qualities, empathy, and excellent coaching and communication skills.</li><li>You’re fluent and comfortable working professionally in English<br><br></li></ul><strong>Bonus points 🥸<br><br></strong><ul><li>Familiarity or experience with Golang (this is a plus but not mandatory</li><li>.Experience working closely with Performance optimization and developer experience</li><li>.Previous use of or exposure to engineer-focused developer portals such as Backstage</li><li>Understanding of regulatory or compliance considerations (like GDPR, PCI-DSS, ISO27001, etc.)<br><br></li></ul><strong>Why now is a particularly exciting time to join Back Market:<br><br></strong><ul><li>🌍 Global reach: Work with teams distributed across the EU, US, and APAC</li><li>🤩 Talented colleagues: Lead an experienced infrastructure team as part of our wider collaborative CloudOPS group</li><li>♻️ True sustainability focus: Directly improve engineering cost-efficiency and actively contribute to reducing our carbon footprint</li><li>📈 Clear data-driven impact: See the direct impact and adoption of your team’s services through measurable results</li><li>🚀 Exciting growth: Join at a thrilling moment as our current EM moves upwards internally, stepping into a mature and impactful role<br><br></li></ul><strong>Recruitment process <br><br></strong><ul><li>Intro call with one of our Talent Acquisition partners - 45 min</li><li>Leadership principles interview with Romain and Sami - 60 min</li><li>Q&amp;A about Infrastructure with 2 DevOps engineer - 45 min</li><li>Technical assessment - 45 min</li><li>Stakeholders interview with Guillaume and Alex - 60 min</li><li>Cultural fit with Paul, VP of Platform - 45 min<br><br></li></ul>Are you hesitating to apply because you don't tick all the boxes? Apply anyway 🌈<br><br><strong>W