 &amp; Education<br><br></strong><ul><li>Provide on-site support during product launches, clinical cases, and distributor onboarding.</li><li>Serve as a clinical expert and resource for troubleshooting and advanced product usage.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Cross-Functional Collaboration<br><br></strong><ul><li>Partner with Sales, Clinical Affairs, Regulatory, and Marketing to align training initiatives with business goals.</li><li>Support KOL development and physician education programs.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Continuous Improvement<br><br></strong><ul><li>Monitor industry trends, competitor training strategies, and customer feedback to continuously improve training offerings.</li><li>Maintain up-to-date knowledge of clinical procedures, guidelines, and best practices in structural heart and interventional cardiology.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Life Sciences, Nursing, Biomedical Engineering, or related field.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of experience in medical device training, preferably in cardiovascular or structural heart domains.</li><li>Proven experience in developing and delivering training programs for diverse audiences.</li><li>Strong understanding of cath lab environments, interventional cardiology procedures, and structural heart interventions.</li><li>Excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Proficiency in digital training tools, LMS platforms, and multimedia content creation.</li><li>Willingness to travel (up to 50%) domestically and internationally.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Skills<br><br></strong><ul><li>Clinical background (e.g., RN, RT, EP tech) or experience in supporting live cases.</li><li>Multilingual capabilities are a plus.</li><li>Familiarity with SavvyWire and OptoWire technologies or similar guidewire systems.<br><br></li></ul>EEO Policy Statement",
