pportunities, profitability, trade terms, securing sites, promotions and launches</li><li>Build collaborative working relationships with retailer and distributor partners at all levels (buyers, marketing, operations)</li><li>Develop and/or coordinate with global teams to build and maintain demand/supply plans to ensure adequate stock levels</li></ul><p><strong>Analytics:</strong></p><ul><li>Analyse sales by SKU and by door and generate weekly sales reports to share with the executive team</li><li>Analyse sales trends, product opportunities and monitor competition, gathering current marketplace information on pricing, products, delivery schedules, merchandising equipment, techniques, etc. to make more informed recommendations for the business</li></ul><p><strong>Drive retail sales:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage daily and weekly sales, monitoring performance against sales targets and profitability and ensuring adequate stock levels, replenishment and promotional orders</li><li>Develop alternative strategies to drive sales where required</li></ul><p><strong>Trade and retail marketing:</strong></p><ul><li>Negotiate trade and retail marketing opportunities with retailers</li><li>Lead execution of all trade marketing, with support from global VM and creative teams</li><li>Align and collaborate with Marketing Director EU on trade marketing budgets and goals</li><li>Measure ROI of any trade opportunities and advise on which opportunities will drive the most commercial value</li></ul><p><strong>Communications</strong>:</p><ul><li>Communicate critical business information to the appropriate internal contacts for action</li><li>Liaise with all internal departments – marketing, finance, logistics to ensure that the account receives the appropriate level of support and all activities result in orders and in-store execution</li></ul><p><strong>Manage the education strategy and field team across the EU:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for recruitment, training and management of sales