AGAGEP) i.e. ASME, API, NACE, etc. At least 15 years of working experience including leadership positions in asset integrity/maintenance and reliability positions on operating industrial plants, preferably in highly hazardous/heavy manufacturing industries such as oil &amp; gas, petrochemical, chemical, or metal processing. Experience in developing procedures to define key system requirements as well as audit protocols, KPIs, and governance mechanisms to monitor the effectiveness of the implementation of Asset Integrity Management across all sub-elements. Exceptional interpersonal skills and team-working attitude to be able to work in multi-cultural and multidisciplinary teams. Problem-solving and flexibility to analyse and adapt to situations Effective leadership skills to drive execution in complex environments. Strong/effective verbal and written communication to be able to interact at different levels of the organization, from executives down to front-line technicians and operators. Fluency in both written and spoken English, in addition to business level proficiency in French. Ability to travel extensively up to 80 % of monthly time.The role is remote based and could be located in one of the following locations: Spain, UK, France, Germany, Portugal, Italy, Belgium or Switzerland.Diversity and InclusionDSS is committed to a diverse workforce and believes this is essential to strengthen our company and drive sustainable growth. We are committed and driving accountability for growing DSS through diversity. Diversity is an indispensable part of our organization's culture. The goal of our commitment to inclusion, dignity, and equal opportunity has not only become a competitive advantage for us but has attracted highly capable and talented employees to DSS.dss+ Core Valuesdss+ works with clients to save lives and create a sustainable future. To do so effectively, we live our core values that underpin our thinking, our goals and our actions, every step of the way. Cou