  "descriptionHtml": "<strong><strong>Job Description:</strong></strong> <strong> About us </strong>ATR is the <strong>world's number one aircraft manufacturer in regional aviation</strong> providing a new generation of turboprops. We are a joint venture between <strong>two European aeronautical heavyweights, Airbus and Leonardo. </strong>From the world’s largest cities, to our planet’s most remote regions<strong>, our purpose is to deliver air travel</strong> to people, communities and businesses in an <strong>innovative, sustainable and modern way.</strong> If you strive for excellence, are driven by <strong>ambition</strong>, <strong>trust </strong>and <strong>respect</strong> as we are, then get your career off to a flighting start with ATR! <strong>Our leadership profile: People Centric Entrepreneurial Inspiring Exemplary Innovative Humble </strong><strong> At ATR y </strong><strong>ou will work with passionate colleagues to make a difference in a human size company with attractive advantages! </strong>We are looking for a Supply Officer to come onboard in our Operations and Procurement Directorate in Fabrice’s team : a team of 10 collaborators! Career Path: Expert <strong> Your Mission </strong> As part of the Supply Chain team and reporting to Head of FAL OEM Supply Chain, you are accountable for the FAL and Partners delivery performance of your supplier portfolio containing systems, cabin and/or propulsion elements:  -OTD performance &amp; associated improvement plan  -Supplier Industrial capacity and risks mapping  -Associated action plan, for production &amp; delivery ramp up  -Crisis mitigation &amp; recovery Responsible &amp; accountable for reporting to your internal stakeholders (program, procurement, configuration...) and internal customers (FAL, program, partners). Active contributor to the ATR and ATR Supply chain continuous improvement plan, leading several improvement projects Within a Multi-Functional Team, you drive your suppliers to reach operational excellence by a lean approach on the supply chain processes, defining, implementing and maintaining the appropriate ATR supplier governance.  You encourage supplier anticipation and secure the production ramp-up.  Your positive energy and “can do attitude” is motivating your colleagues to work beyond boundaries of organizations and/or functions as one ATR team to achieve common objectives.  You promote an open feedback culture to encounter trust and continuous development  You communicate efficiently with our internal customers and management, as well as with the supplier organization by visiting them regularly. Main activities:  -Monitor, KPI &amp; data driven, and secure On Time Delivery of systems &amp; equipment to FAL and partners  -Manage ordering process (purchase order and procurement plan) with a collaborative approach with international suppliers to fit with production need date of the different ATR production sites (Leonardo, Airbus Atlantic and FAL) through Airsupply portal starting by forecast mastering and masterdata management  -Monitor Suppliers work in progress status, Missing Parts and KPIs and initiate  -Evaluate the capacity, skills and performance of suppliers with a short term and long term view  -Perform effective overall monitoring of supplier activities, with a good understanding of the overall situation and scope of suppliers.  -Identify suppliers’ industrial risks and suggest mitigation security measures if necessary  -Negotiate and drumbeat recovery plan with low performance suppliers.  -Provide a global vision of the volume of stocks and implement action plans with suppliers in order to control the level.  -Escalate internally, including to the buyer for claim application and all relevant functions  -Act as a supply chain focal point and coordinate various MFT or transversal projects with internal and external stakeholders  -Lead meeting breakdown structure to monitor suppliers performances (daily, weekly, monthly).  -Lead continu