rgy and “can do attitude” is motivating your colleagues to work beyond boundaries of organizations and/or functions as one ATR team to achieve common objectives.  You promote an open feedback culture to encounter trust and continuous development  You communicate efficiently with our internal customers and management, as well as with the supplier organization by visiting them regularly. Main activities:  -Monitor, KPI &amp; data driven, and secure On Time Delivery of systems &amp; equipment to FAL and partners  -Manage ordering process (purchase order and procurement plan) with a collaborative approach with international suppliers to fit with production need date of the different ATR production sites (Leonardo, Airbus Atlantic and FAL) through Airsupply portal starting by forecast mastering and masterdata management  -Monitor Suppliers work in progress status, Missing Parts and KPIs and initiate  -Evaluate the capacity, skills and performance of suppliers with a short term and long term view  -Perform effective overall monitoring of supplier activities, with a good understanding of the overall situation and scope of suppliers.  -Identify suppliers’ industrial risks and suggest mitigation security measures if necessary  -Negotiate and drumbeat recovery plan with low performance suppliers.  -Provide a global vision of the volume of stocks and implement action plans with suppliers in order to control the level.  -Escalate internally, including to the buyer for claim application and all relevant functions  -Act as a supply chain focal point and coordinate various MFT or transversal projects with internal and external stakeholders  -Lead meeting breakdown structure to monitor suppliers performances (daily, weekly, monthly).  -Lead continuous improvement transverse actions / project, to improve efficiency and proceed to the transformation needed to secure our ramp-up.About YouMinimum of 7 years of experience in supply chain management and lean manufacturingGraduate degree 