lease (and beyond). You’re empowered to make decisions and trusted to do what’s right for the product</li><li>Build smart, ship fast: We deploy to production around 70 times a week. You’ll help us keep that rhythm by balancing speed, quality, and business impact</li><li>Be a partner, not an executor: You bring strong opinions, backed by experience and you’re not afraid to challenge the status quo when it makes sense</li><li>Level up the team: You share knowledge, put in place pair programming when it’s needed, review code with care, and bring others along on your journey. You help raise the bar<br><br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Our Tech Stack<br><br></strong><ul><li>Frontend: TypeScript, Vue.js, Nuxt, Zeroheight</li><li>Backend: Kotlin, Java Spring Boot, Gradle, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Elasticsearch, RabbitMQ, Redis</li><li>Platform: Google Cloud Platform, Kubernetes, Datadog Terraform, ArgoCD, Gitlab CI</li><li>Mobile: Flutter, Swift, Kotlin</li><li>Data: BigQuery, Looker, Spark, Python<br><br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Life @Malt<br><br></strong><ul><li>Remote Culture: Strong remote culture with most of the team working full-remote throughout Europe</li><li>Guild Days: Technical guilds: Practice sharing, continuous training, experimentation and technology watch</li><li>Tech Conferences: Annual Malt Tech Days, organized and presented by Malt’s engineering team. Opportunity to attend major tech conferences</li><li>Career Path: Detailed career path allowing you to set achievable objectives and progress over time<br><br><br><br></li></ul><strong>About You 🧑‍🚀<br><br></strong><ul><li>You have 6+ years of professional experience in software development, with a first experience in a product company (SaaS, fintech, marketplace…)</li><li>You're highly proficient in Java or Kotlin, and comfortable navigating complex backend architecture, APIs, and data models</li><li>You have a first experience working with Typescripts and eager to learn Nuxt and Vue.js</li><li>You have a “Product Engineer” approach: You think beyond the code. You’re curious about the “why” behind features, and you're proactive in proposing improvements and owning delivery from A to Z</li><li>You build with pragmatism: You know how to adapt your practices to the context. You have excellent knowledge of modern architecture, but you also know when you need to move fast and build disposable code</li><li>Autonomy: You are committed to improving the team's practices and know how to adapt your methods to suit the context</li><li>You own the whole lifecycle: building CI/CD, testing, observability, monitoring. Shipping is just one step. You make sure what you build works, lasts, and scales</li><li>Fluent in English, you are comfortable speaking and writing in an English-speaking environment<br><br><br><br></li></ul><strong>How to join the mission? 🚀<br><br></strong><ul><li>Screening with Alex, our Talent Acquisition Manager, to better understand your background, aspirations and answer your questions (45 minutes)</li><li>Interview with one of our Engineering Manager, to discuss your experience and the role in more detail (75 minutes)</li><li>Technical Home assignment to prepare and present in order to evaluate your hard skills</li><li>Final interview with Jean (VP Engineering) to discuss Malt’s long term vision (45 minutes)<br><br><br><br></li></ul>We will send you an interview guide so you can best prepare yourself<br><br>At Malt, we are committed to fostering an inclusive and diverse workplace. We recruit based on skills, experience, and potential, without any form of discrimination related to age, gender, sexual orientation, ethnicity, religion, or disability. Our mission is to create a work environment where everyone feels valued, respected, and safe to thrive.",
